<br>
The downside as you have said is the inability to be activley playing both characters at once, so idealy you need one of the cahracters to be a passive class, while the other is aggressive.  Some combos that are great but wouldnt work in this situation are Bards and Wizards for example.<br>
<br>
Here are some great combos for people playing two characters at once;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Warrior - Druid</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This is a nice combo because the druid can keep up with heals, but more importantly you get damage shields, sows, evacs, personal transit service <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , and a nice array of buffs and SNARES! (cant stress that enough).  Plus tracking is nice for questing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Warrior - Cleric</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
At later levels the complete healing and uber buffs alows you to tear things apart and never stop.  The hard part is getting there, as I'm sure you have experienced.  More combat potential than the Druid, but you sacrifice utility.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Monk - Shaman</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Simply my favorite combination for playing two at once, or duo'ing with real people.  Shamans can buff, haste you, slow the mob, and regen.  Combine with the crazyness of monks and their natural regen and you have a deadly combo.  Also once you get the Shaman high enough level you can toss the pet in for added help.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Monk / Warrior - Mage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A rather odd combo that relys on the pet assisting while the Mage drops DDs, DOTS, or Rains as available, and summons bandages to keep the Monk or Warrior healthy.  don't forget the Damage Shields!.<br>
<br>
Alternativley what some people do is have a Mage on a second account who simply summons a billion bandages and hands them off to the Warrior or Monk who then proceeds to solo until they run out of bandages.  Rinse &amp; Repeat.  Works best for Monks in my experience (This is a tactic I use on FV to solo, since you dont really need to level the Mage much, just enough to get the spells Summon Bandages and Dimensional Pocket)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Any Tank - Beastlord</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Bestlords really don't do much besides let their beast attack anyway.  Beastlords also receive minor buff's and heals.  Not the best Duo IMO, but it is interesting none the less <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Any Tank - Necromancer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Perhaps not the best duo, but interesting.  As a full fledged tank you solve the largest problem Necro's have, keeping things off of them.  The necro could then focus on DOTing, Liching, and Taping as necessary while using their reverse taps to keep the tank alive.  May not be entirley viable.<br>
<br>
Can;t think of any others at the moment, will post more if I think of any <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Falzure <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 4:14:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1493.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curious - who plays two characters at once?</span><hr size=1> Well I used to Dual comp a shaman and a druid.  I personally find that dual comping is too much like work, unless one of the characters is very passive.. EG cleric/warrior, druid/shaman.  I play with my girlfriend as a shaman monk duo.  To be honest its a ridiculous combination and should probably be nerfed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  We do things that I would have been cautious of in whole groups in the same level...    The few times one of us leaves the room, though, the other is left running both for a few minutes.  Doable, but alot of switching back and forth for monk/shaman.<br>
